Haakon Riiser wrote:
> The following "bug" is probably not important, since it only
> happens in a syntactically illegal command, but I chose to report
> it anyway, in case the bug has other (more serious) symptomps.
> 
> Steps to reproduce:
> 
>   % zsh -f
>   % alias foo='foo bar'
>   % (foo) foo
>   zsh: parse error near `foo'
>   % history
>       1  alias foo='foo bar'
>       2  (foo) foo bar
>                ^^^^^^^

Actually, I think it's relatively harmless because it only shows up when
parsing output after an error.  However, I think we can get it right
quite easily, too.

